16 (B) For taxable years beginning on or after January 1, 2026, to the extent any amount
17 was taken by a corporation as a deduction allowed by Section 179 of the Internal
18 Revenue Code in connection with any single-family residential rental property, such
19 amount shall be added to the taxable income of the corporation."
20 SECTION 2.
21 Said chapter is further amended by revising paragraph (15) of subsection (a) of Code Section
22 48-7-27, relating to computation of taxable income, as follows:
23 "(15)(A) The deduction provided and allowed by Section 179 of the Internal Revenue
24 Code of 1986 as enacted on or before January 1, 2005, to the extent the deduction has
25 not been included in federal adjusted gross income, as defined under the Internal
26 Revenue Code of 1986, and the expenses have not been included in itemized
27 nonbusiness deductions; provided, however, that for taxable years beginning on or after
28 January 1, 2026, the provisions of this subparagraph shall not be applicable for
29 single-family residential rental property.
30 (B) For taxable years beginning on or after January 1, 2026, to the extent any amount
31 was taken by a corporation as a deduction allowed by Section 179 of the Internal
32 Revenue Code in connection with any single-family residential rental property, such
33 amount shall be added to the taxable income of the corporation."
34 SECTION 3.
35 This Act shall become effective on January 1, 2026, and shall be applicable to all taxable
36 years beginning on or after such date.
37 SECTION 4.
38 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
